{"name": "asyncudp", "metadata": {"name": "asyncudp", "version": "0.11.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/eerimoq/asyncudp", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Asyncio high level UDP sockets.", "upload_time": 1690209930}, "documentation": ["# Asyncio high level UDP sockets\n\nAsyncio high level UDP sockets.\n\nProject homepage: <https://github.com/eerimoq/asyncudp>\n\nDocumentation: <https://asyncudp.readthedocs.org/en/latest>\n\n# Installation\n\n```python\n$ pip install asyncudp\n```\n\n# Example client\n\n```python\nimport asyncio\nimport asyncudp\n\nasync def main():\n    sock = await asyncudp.create_socket(remote_addr=('127.0.0.1', 9999))\n    sock.sendto(b'Hello!')\n    print(await sock.recvfrom())\n    sock.close()\n\nasyncio.run(main())\n```\n\n# Example server\n\n```python\nimport asyncio\nimport asyncudp\n\nasync def main():\n    sock = await asyncudp.create_socket(local_addr=('127.0.0.1', 9999))\n\n    while True:\n        data, addr = await sock.recvfrom()\n        print(data, addr)\n        sock.sendto(data, addr)\n\nasyncio.run(main())\n```\n\n# Test\n\n```\n$ python3 -m unittest\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "asyncudp.version", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "asyncudp.version.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "asyncudp", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "asyncudp.create_socket", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "local_addr", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "remote_addr", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "packets_queue_max_size", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "reuse_port", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a UDP socket with given local and remote addresses.\n\n```pycon\n>>> sock = await asyncudp.create_socket(local_addr=('127.0.0.1', 